20a%20set%20number%20of%20hours%20or%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Echhur-pon%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20responsible%20for%20opening%20and%20closing%20the%20water%20channels%20to%20ensure%20fair%20distribution.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20rotation%20is%20usually%20determined%20by%20the%20size%20of%20land%20holdings%2C%20with%20larger%20farms%20receiving%20proportionally%20more%20water%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20system%20is%20flexible%20and%20can%20be%20adjusted%20based%20on%20seasonal%20water%20availability%20and%20crop%20needs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECommunity%20meetings%20are%20held%20to%20discuss%20and%20resolve%20any%20disputes%20or%20changes%20needed%20in%20the%20water%20allocation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndigenous%20engineering%20techniques%2C%20such%20as%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20(%3Cem%3Ema-yur%2C%20yu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20showcase%20local%20ingenuity%20in%20adapting%20to%20challenging%20terrains.%20By%20studying%20and%20applying%20such%20local%20engineering%20knowledge%2C%20we%20can%20develop%20context-appropriate%20irrigation%20solutions%20elsewhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20do%20these%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20work%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EMa-yur%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E(mother%20canal)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20the%20main%20canal%20that%20diverts%20water%20from%20glacier-fed%20streams.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20typically%20built%20along%20contour%20lines%20to%20maintain%20a%20gentle%20slope%20for%20water%20flow.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20often%20lined%20with%20stones%20to%20prevent%20seepage%20and%20erosion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20stretch%20for%20several%20kilometres%2C%20bringing%20water%20to%20multiple%20villages.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EYu-ra%20